Study

Logical isolation, not network isolation.
Default namespaces: default, kube-system, kube-public, kube-node-lease.
ResourceQuota (per-namespace limits) vs LimitRange (per-pod/container defaults).
Hands-On

kubectl create namespace dev
kubectl config set-context --current --namespace=dev
kubectl apply -f - <<EOF
apiVersion: v1
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata: {name: dev-quota, namespace: dev}
spec:
  hard:
    pods: "10"
    requests.cpu: "2"
    requests.memory: 2Gi
    limits.cpu: "4"
    limits.memory: 4Gi
EOF
kubectl describe quota -n dev

